      "full_name": "Gabrelyanov Aram Ashotovich",
      "is_primary": true
    }
  ],
  "remarks": "Aram Gabrelyanov is a Russian propagandist close to the Kremlin. He is spreading aggressive propaganda, by disseminating fake news and misinformation in support of Russia’s war of aggression against Ukraine. He is the founder and editorial director of Life news portal, which has become one of the symbols of unscrupulous propaganda. He himself has spoken aggressively and in a biased manner against the democratically elected authorities of Ukraine and has always emphasised his full support for Russia’s aggressive policy towards Ukraine. He has been actively involved in multiple projects conducted in occupied Ukrainian territories for media specialists, such as the “Academy of Emotions” funded by the Presidential Fund for Cultural Initiatives and established to promote the war. His company Mash manages regional publications of the Mash propaganda project. He is also a sponsor of the WarGonzo Z-military project, whose correspondents have been conducting anti-Ukrainian propaganda since the beginning of the war. Therefore, Aram Gabrelyanov is supporting and implementing actions and policies which undermine and threaten the territorial integrity, sovereignty and independence of Ukraine.",
  "birth_info": [
